Governor Mai Mala Buni of Yobe State has approved the appointment of former attorney-general and commissioner for justice, Mr. Mustapha Goniri, as the pro chancellor and chairman of the Governing Council of Yobe State University (YSU). Goniri’s appointment was contained in a statement issued by the press secretary to the secretary to the state government (SSG), Shu’aibu Abdullahi. The governor also named a former member of the House of Representatives representing Nguru, Machina, Karasuwa and Yusufari federal constituency, Hon. Baba Bukar Machinama, Musa Usman, and  a former commissioner and adviser to the governor, Hon. Zakariya Maimalari, as members of the council. Abdullahi said that “the appointment takes immediate effect.”